<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Discipline2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Discipline,</orth> vb. to train, to instruct: <cit><quote>--d, ay, dieted in grace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 261" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 261</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he that --d thy arms to fight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.255" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 255</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>has he --d Aufidius soundly?</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 139</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>